rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going pretty well. critical_positive: I think what worked well is we both had some movie and TV common interests. And both of us were friendly people who had done a study like this before. I think we both also built off of each other when we could - giving recommendations on shows, or asking about vacation plans.
critical_negative: Sometimes I felt my partner was a little low energy, but it also sounded like there had been a recent death in her family so I don't think it had anything to do with our conversation, and had more to do with her own personal circumstances. Otherwise I think this went well for a talk between strangers.

rest_of_day_open: I see it as being fun and exciting because I work for a mission thrift store and I love to help people and meet people. I feel better about my life after hearing what my chat partner had been through. Maybe it is a bit easier not to worry because I see other people getting through situations.
critical_positive: We found some commonalities and discussed those and it worked out well when I told her some of the things I had been through and she understood and had been through something worse. It was a refreshing discussion after being under lock down so long. I am really glad you found this chat partner for me.
critical_negative: It was a bit challenging to find the commonalities to begin with but once we chatted a few minutes, they began to show up. We discussed movies that we enjoy and then some things about our lives that we have learned. It was a progression, the beginning was a bit slow, but then it speeded up.
